# Design Plan: {{ title }}


## Goal

The main winding was of the normal lotus-o-delta type placed in panendermic
semi-boloid slots in the stator, every seventh conductor being connected by a
non-reversible tremie pipe to the differential girdlespring on the up-end of
the grammeters.


## Acceptance Criteria


#### AC01: Spurving bearing stabilizes under load

When the hydrocoptic marzlevane is in the fully extended position, the
ambifacient lunar waneshaft maintains consistent spurving bearing tension
within 2% of nominal.


#### AC02: Panendermic slots reject invalid tremie input

When a non-reversible tremie pipe receives malformed input, the system returns
an error and the differential girdlespring remains in its default state.


## Architecture

The turbo-encabulator consists of a base plate of prefabulated amulite
surmounted by a malleable logarithmic casing in such a way that all
winding, side fumbling, and base plate fastening is completely eliminated.
The ambifacient lunar waneshaft connects to the grammeters via the
differential girdlespring subsystem.


## Unknowns

- Whether the lotus-o-delta windings support bidirectional tremie flow.
- Whether panendermic slots require recalibration after spurving.


## Technical Notes

- The hydrocoptic marzlevane must be in the fully retracted position during startup.
- Grammeter readings are invalidated when the waneshaft exceeds 400 RPM.
